 ’em because they are against the landowners. And moles.”

“What about sparrows?” I asked with great gentleness. “Are they ‘against’ as you put it?”

“A sparrow is a beggar among birds—a real street-beggar. A beggar,” he repeated again and again, now leaning with both hands on his stick and swaying a little. It was obvious he considered himself to be an extraordinarily astute arguer. No, he was not merely a fool, he was a fool of the melancholic type. Even his smile was glu